  "texts": [
    "These involve uniformly (in k-space) polarizing any four orthogonal directions within the Chern quartets.",
    "One example would be polarizing into all the A bands, which would yield a valley Hall state with net vanishing Chern number.",
    "Acting with independent U (4) rotations within the Chern quartets generates the continuous manifold of C = 0 states.",
    "We can similarly obtain ground states with total Chern number |C| = 2, 4 by unequally occupying the two Chern quartets 41.",
    "These Slater determinants can all be referred to as generalized ferromagnets [33,35], and highlight the resemblance to QHFM."
